Where does the disease control reform go after the epidemic

By Danni Peng and Wei Qian

PUBLISHED: March 2,2020

On January 23,2020, the city of Wuhan was closed, marking the 18th anniversary of the founding of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) . At the same time, China's disease control system ushered in the second great test after "sars" -- this is a more severe test.

A week later, Li Liming, the founder of China's CDC and a professor at public health, was called back to lead a team of leading figures in the country's public health field, to provide the relevant departments of the epidemic prevention and control situation of the study, prevention and control technical support.

Li Liming, who led the CDC in the fight against SARS, was asked if the current direction of the disease control system had come true. He said simply, "not very satisfied. ".

Surface improvement

Li Liming, who worked as a POSTDOC at the nation's No. 1 Johns Hopkins University, has a clear vision of what a CDC should look like. On January 23,2002, the inauguration ceremony of the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention was held in the Great Hall of the People. Li Liming obtained 2,400 quotas from the editorial office, and transferred 18 business cadres from across the country to establish a relatively complete institutional framework for Disease Control and Prevention, even though at that time it was still a blank in several prevention and control fields, such as sexually transmitted diseases, AIDS and tuberculosis, have set up their own agencies. Unlike the U.S. CDC, which started as an infectious disease center, China's CDC has the most comprehensive centers for Disease Research at birth, a high point.

The outbreak of SARS 11 months after the listing of the National CDC made governments, especially the central government, aware of the importance of disease control. After the outbreak, ten billion yuan went into public health, and the disease control system, which had previously been largely ignored, changed dramatically.

Yang Weizhong, a former deputy director of the CDC, said in an interview with China Newsweek that the CDC Office for Disease Control and emergency response, which he previously headed, used to have fewer than 10 people and an annual budget of more than 3 million. After SARS, it expanded to more than 50 people, funding increased to more than 100 million yuan. A number of high-level Biosafety laboratories began to be built, high-end equipment has been continuously deployed, laboratory testing capacity, epidemiological investigation capacity and on-site disposal capacity have been rapidly improved.

Hence the remarks made by Takatomi, the current director of the CDC and an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, at the national "two sessions" in 2019. At that time, "people often ask me, 'will SARS come again after more than ten years? ' " Takatomi told the media confidently? "SARS is a virus that can appear at any time, but I am confident that it will not happen again, because our infectious disease surveillance network is well established and it will not happen again. "

Takatomi was the first academician to hold the position of director of China's CDC. In the 18 years since the establishment of the CDC, there have been only three directors. The first two directors, Li Liming and Wang Yu, were both from medical backgrounds. The latter served as the director for 13 years, during which the major public health event was the 2013 H7N9 bird flu epidemic in Jiangsu, Anhui and other places.

TAKATOMI's main areas of research include envelope viruses and structural immunology, emerging and re emerging infectious diseases, represented by influenza, to study the characteristics of molecular evolution, host interaction, cross-species transmission mechanism, virus-specific t cell immunity and molecular recognition of important envelope viruses. COVID-19 belongs to the envelope virus, which means that Takatomi's team happens to be one of the most authoritative in China for studying the new coronavirus.

Takatomi, who holds eight academician titles, has certainly been successful as a scientist. "Takatomi, who trained at Oxford and Harvard, is very smart, he is loved by his peers around the world, and as the leader of the C.D.C. , he is first class, " said a longtime foreign observer of public health

In 2011, Takatomi became deputy director of the National CDC, and in August 2017, Wang Yu stepped down because he reached the age limit, and Takatomi took over as director. Before the new outbreak, Takatomi's notable feat at the CDC was his leadership of Operation Ebola. For Infectious Disease Prevention and control, Takatomi has been pursuing a "threshold forward" strategy. If the epidemic in Africa is not contained, it is only a matter of time before Ebola enters China, given the global integration and high level of transportation, he said. So in 2014, the Chinese CDC sent a team led by Takatomi to Sierra Leone to help with virus research and outbreak control.

However, with the Wuhan outbreak, Takatomi and his CDC faced an unprecedented crisis of confidence. Many people believe that the CDC has information about the outbreak but did not take timely measures to deal with it, and did not timely public disclosure. Although CDC officials later came forward with some clarification, it did not go well.

In the eyes of National CDC employees, Takatomi is an optimistic, extroverted leader. But his "optimistic" remarks, in the tense and even dignified early days of the epidemic, did not sound timely. For example, in his only two appearances at the press conference, he first said that "children are not susceptible" , which was soon overturned by the fact that children with new pneumonia were diagnosed, and then he said, "This vaccine, I can say with confidence, will definitely succeed. " These comments, was picked out by netizens repeatedly retweeted and commented.

Wang Hua, president of Jiangsu Preventive Medicine Association, served as Director of Jiangsu Provincial Center for Disease Control and deputy director of the provincial health and Family Planning Commission. He pointed out that, under the Infectious Disease Prevention Act, only the National Health Administration and its delegated provincial health administration have the power to publicize outbreaks, the National Center for Disease Control and Prevention and local centers for Disease Control and Prevention do not have the authority to release the epidemic. The CDC is the Decision Support Agency, but it doesn't make decisions.

One CDC practitioner was struck by the CDC's predicament. Compared to front line doctors, the CDC has no authority to prescribe, to organize, to coordinate, and to order, he said. What the CDC can do, is to cooperate with the superior instruction to do a good job of disease prevention and control, do a good job in the laboratory. The disease is contained, the focus is on the front line doctors, the disease is not contained, the board hit the CDC.

From 2003, the establishment of unlimited scenery, to 2020 encounter "gang fight" , China's disease control what happened?

Substantial retrogression

In 2002, after graduating with a degree in preventive medicine from the Peking University Health Science Center (now Peking University Health Science Center) , he moved to the Chongwen District Center for Disease Control and Prevention. At that time, it wasn't called the CDC, it was called the Chongwen District Health and Disease Control Station. The 1990s began in 1953 and has since added chronic disease control, but the core work has been infectious disease control and vaccination.

Epidemic Prevention stations have two main functions, one is health-related disease surveillance, control, publicity, and the other part is the work of administrative supervision, such as issuing health permits. But in 2003, it was renamed the Chongwen District Center for Disease Control and Prevention, with the functions of the epidemic prevention station split in two. health-related work remained at the center, while Health Law Enforcement and administrative supervision were assigned to the health supervision station.

The reforms began in 2001. In that year, the General Office of the Ministry of Health issued the guiding opinions on the reform of the disease prevention and control system, clarifying the functions and tasks of disease prevention and control institutions at all levels, the functions of Health Law Enforcement and supervision entrusted to the former provincial, prefectural (city) and county health and epidemic prevention stations shall be delineated as a whole, and the functions of disease prevention and control, Public Health Technology Management and service in the relevant health institutions shall be centralized, added the prevention and control of chronic diseases and other functions, the health and epidemic prevention station renamed the Center for Disease Control and Prevention, the administrative power of the center has been separated out.

From the day the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention was founded, the agency has been inherently deficient. Li Liming explained that from the initial establishment, the CDC is directly under the Ministry of Health Institutions, no executive power. The National Health Commission also has a disease prevention and Control Bureau, which is the administrative department, and the China Center for Disease Control and Prevention, which is the operational department. "At that time, we had already started the program discussion on the integration of the Ministry of Health's Disease Control Bureau and the National CDC, and had already entered the argumentation stage with the Chinese government, which was stopped due to the SARS epidemic, " Li recalled.

This stagnation caused the CDC to regress further in the years that followed.

At the Chongwen District Center for Disease Control and Prevention, Xu sometimes made more than $10,000 from vaccine sales. Later, he transferred to the National Center for Disease Control and Prevention, although the intermediate title, in 2010, the monthly salary fell by more than 6,000 yuan.

This is because, in 2012, the State Council introduced the reform of public institutions. Institutions providing basic services such as compulsory education, basic scientific research and public health are classified as public welfare. Li Liming explained that the "public welfare category" is that the state gives whatever money is used to complete the national disease control task, and does not allow the development of service-oriented, fee-charging projects. "It turns out that the Chinese Academy of Preventive Medicine (the predecessor of CDC) is in the second category of Public Welfare, and the State is the differential subsidy. The rest of the money can be earned by oneself, for example, by means of medical examinations and social testing services, and by paying performance wages, which can ensure everyone's enthusiasm. "

In addition to a steep drop in revenue, the CDC title promotion is also strictly defined by the proportion of the establishment, promotion channel is also blocked. In those years, Xu felt that more and more people were leaving him, and he left for the company in 2014.

In response, the Chinese Center for Disease Control and Prevention Epidemiology chief scientist Zeng Guang pointed out that in the last three years, the National Center for Disease Control and Prevention alone lost as many as 100 young and middle-aged cadres. In recent years, he said, only 2 percent of graduates from Peking University's Medical Department and Fudan University Shanghai Medical College's public health have joined the CDC, and most of them are not from key universities. "But in reality, we need people who are highly qualified, who understand what is going on at home and abroad and who have a strong sense of enterprise. "

Not only does the CDC workforce lack stability, but the public health talent pool is in dire straits. Hao Yuantao, dean of the Public Health at National Sun Yat-sen University, told China Newsweek that in recent years, the highest proportion of students who volunteered to major in preventive medicine was no more than 30% to 40% . In addition, outstanding graduates of Preventive Medicine major choose few CDC institutions, they would rather go to the hospital to do sense, scientific research or to some related auxiliary departments.

Wang Yu has said that while in theory, national health is a priority and a foundation for everything, in practice, it is hard to see how it can be done. Taking fiscal spending as an example, Zeng Cheng, the former party secretary of the Sichuan University of the public health in Hwaseo, noted that in 2014, the national "Special Task Fund for Public Health" had been allocated $529m; by 2019, the budget had dropped to $450m, year-on-year decrease of 14.9% .

In April 2019, Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People's Congress Chen Zhu called for a high priority to be given to the risk that the functioning of the disease prevention and control system would be weakened in the context of public sector reform. His report also pointed out that the tendency to emphasize medical care over public health has not been corrected, that the number of public health doctors is insufficient and decreasing year by year, and that the talent pool is relatively weak and does not match the "prevention-oriented" approach.

A case in point is Liaoning Province's 2018 disease control reform. At the provincial level, the Liaoning CDC has been retained, but there are different integration plans at the local and municipal levels. For example, in Shenyang, the CDC and health supervision institutions have been integrated into the municipal health services and Administrative Law Enforcement Center; But in Fushun, the CDC is part of the National Institutes of health.

In response, Wang Hua said, "Now everyone is blaming the CDC, just like when the vaccine goes wrong, it doesn't make sense to remove the director of the CDC. We old comrades joked that we might as well go back to the old epidemic prevention station, where the functions of supervision and monitoring were put together. Now that the administrative power is gone, everything depends on how the health administration at the same level makes decisions."

In 2017, Wang Yu, director of the National CDC, said in a somewhat wistful commencement address, "It was an untimely time to graduate, a time when there were no Emerging Infectious Diseases, no public health emergencies, and because of that, public health, disease control, was largely forgotten. This is the old saying 'birds don't fly, good bow Tibet' , which hasn't been used for a long time and people forget it. "

Reform the system, but not just the system

"In many countries around the world, the Ministry of Public Health is known as the Ministry of Public Health. But the Ministry of Health of the People's Republic of China, as it was called in English, removed public. In fact, the function of the National Health Administration Department should be public health management,"Li Liming said. In practice, however, China's health authorities have focused most of their attention on the management of medical institutions. Li Li stressed that the reform of the system is not to solve the current situation of China's public health system all the code, in the reform of the system, but more important is the concept of change.

In Academia, public health is defined as the science and art of preventing disease, prolonging life, promoting physical and mental health and efficiency through organized social efforts. Public Health in a narrow sense refers to the prevention and control of disease, and its supporting discipline is epidemiology. As former CDC director Tom Frieden recently noted, public health, not health care, has taken the biggest responsibility for the world's health over the past 20th century, and these measures range widely, including Tobacco Control, vaccines, clean water, and so on.

However, one epidemiology professor jokes that public health practitioners live in a paradox: when they eliminate a disease, they lose their value. Li Liming also felt this rule very strongly, "preventive medicine, public health is actually a 'self-destructive Great Wall' team, the better your prevention work, the less social and government departments pay attention to you. "

According to Fei Heping, in order to maximize the efficiency of public health organizations at all levels, the five most important elements are: adequate funding, a critical mass of qualified personnel, strong links with other health care entities, effective communication, and technical independence with political support.

On that last point, he explains, the U.S. CDC is a federal agency two steps away from the president, with considerable freedom of action, the CDC's technical expertise is respected in the United States and globally, within and outside government. He said, "As director of the CDC, I have reported to President Obama on key health issues, and this direct approach to the highest levels of government empowers the CDC in the United States and ensures that public health is prioritized at the national level.

How to reform the system? The idea of many public health experts is to give administrative powers to the CDC. Like the fire, in the handling of the epidemic, has its own decision-making power, disposal power. In response, Li Liming figuratively said, "it's impossible to put out a fire in a high-rise building. When I drove there, I first asked the higher-ups what plans we had, and then we went to put out the fire after the higher-ups approved it? " Specifically, he hoped, the reform of the disease control system can refer to the current Chinese Medicine Administration and the Drug Administration. In the future, the disease control and prevention will be under the direct control of the State Council, and a National Disease Control and Prevention Administration with administrative management and professional technical support will be established, to further strengthen the role and functions of CDC departments in Handling Public Health Affairs.

Funding for the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention in China has been declining over the years, Zhang Zuofeng, associate dean of the Public Health at Ucla and a senior tenured professor of epidemiology, told China Newsweek, because is the public institution, also does not have the method to have the income from other places, the disease control personnel's income also drops greatly. "So there are a lot of outstanding young brain drain at the CDC, and there are some questions about whether such a team can effectively control the epidemic. "

Zhang style that to strengthen the public health system, it is important to turn the disease control system into a stand-alone system, like the CDC. "The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, first, can publish data, and second, has the power to declare a state of emergency to begin disease control. So I propose that we bring the disease control system into government orbit, into an independent government system, with the CDC in charge of the control of acute infectious diseases and chronic diseases, so that we can seize the opportunity, act in a timely manner, and eliminate the disease from the very beginning."

Ren Jun, former director of the CDC in Anhui Province, said the CDC has a good tradition and should not be given up lightly. For example, there used to be a rule that the head of a CDC unit had to be an undergraduate in public health. But I don't seem to be following that rule anymore.

"In this case, a lot of cadres were dealt with on the spot. In fact, in many places, the first and second leaders of the Health Commission do not have a medical background or a public health education background, which surprised me because it is a position that requires strong professional knowledge,"said Jiang Qingwu, a professor of epidemiology and former dean of the public health at the Fudan University, hubei epidemic early various problems, and this "not professional people are doing professional things" phenomenon has a certain relationship.

In contrast, all state health directors in the United States are generally MD plus MPH, which is the best educational background for Health Administration, Li said. "I understand that about a quarter of MDS in medical schools in the United States have MPH degrees, reflecting the importance of public health and its place and role in the U.S. health care system, which is a popular vocational education, " he said.

But the shift in perception is both administrative and public. For example, he says, after Emerging Infectious Diseases, it should be susceptible to everyone, not to any other group; how could it not be transmitted from person to person? It's just a matter of time, and if clinicians and even the general public, had this kind of common sense, then the early prevention and control of NCP wouldn't have come to this.

Fei pointed out that each country needed to have the capacity to prevent, detect and respond effectively to disease outbreaks, and that the larger the country, the more resources needed to do so.

Huang Qifan, vice chairman of the China Center for international economic exchanges and former mayor of Chongqing, recently wrote that we have already seen the trillions in economic losses caused by such a public health event, so it is worth investing one hundred billion RMB over five to 10 years to establish and improve a national public health and epidemic prevention system.

"China has made remarkable efforts to understand and contain the new crown disease, " former CDC director Fei Heping wrote. After SARS, China's public health system became more powerful. People like me working in global public health hope that, just as SARS enabled China to strengthen its disease control system and invest in it, the current situation will lead to another exponential leap in China's public health capacity."

Xu was given a pseudonym at the request of the interviewee
